ON MONDAY morning, a man (27) died after being struck by a vehicle in Honeydew, north-west of Joburg. ER24 spokesman Werner Vermaak said paramedics arrived on the scene at 6.30am and found a body on the pavement. He said the vehicle that hit the man was parked opposite the road. “Paramedics found the man had a head injury and was declared dead.” The driver of the vehicle was assessed and had no injuries. “Details surrounding the incident are not yet known, but local authorities were on the scene for further investigation.” Also on Monday, 12 people were hospitalised after a collision in Observatory in Joburg. Emer-G-Med workers attended the scene and took them to hospital for further treatment. Cops are investigating. Netcare 911 spokesman Shawn Herbst said a man and woman died. “A man who was in the station wagon was taken to hospital,” he said. Herbst said technicians and rescue workers had to use the Jaws of Life to free the bodies. Circumstances leading to the accident would be investigated.